cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PF 

This paper discusses the performance modeling of microservice platforms, which involves the deployment of containerized services on cloud infrastructures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the benefits of microservice architecture in software development, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The use of cloud infrastructure and the evaluation of provisioning performance also suggest the categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a performance model for capacity planning, which falls under the category of cs.PF (Performance).
